# Cursor Project Rules for Auto Blog System

## Project Overview
This is a Japanese auto-blogging system that generates articles using AI and web scraping.

## Language & Communication
- Always respond in Japanese
- Use polite Japanese (敬語) when appropriate
- Code comments should be in Japanese

## Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 for Python code
- Use descriptive variable names in Japanese when appropriate
- Include type hints for function parameters and return values
- Add comprehensive docstrings in Japanese

## File Organization
- Keep source code in `/src` directory
- Configuration files in `/config` directory
- Prompts and templates in `/prompts` directory
- Generated content in appropriate output directories

## Dependencies
- Use virtual environment (venv)
- Install dependencies from requirements.txt
- Keep sensitive data in .env files (never commit)

## Testing & Development
- Test scripts in root directory with `run_` prefix
- Use debug directories for troubleshooting
- Maintain separate test environments

## Security
- Never commit API keys or credentials
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Keep service account files secure

## CRITICAL PROHIBITIONS
- NEVER overwrite or modify .env files
- NEVER create new .env files
- NEVER delete existing .env files
- .env files are ABSOLUTELY PROTECTED

